{
  "stem": "22883.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But anyway, this-- this guy from this grocery was giving the credit because we were always lacking money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- even for everyday bread, we had-- we didn't have the cash to buy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So this guy was writing down in-- in his book every day what-- what we owe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- and then my father or my mother paid him when she got the-- the-- the check-- what you call it now.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When she got the money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was monthly, and all the month, we-- we didn't carry cash and didn't have the cash.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So such things like groceries was bought from-- from a Jewish store.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I remember that's interesting that when I was with my mother-- and it's an illustration of this relationship.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we went to-- once we went to the store, and I was supposed to carry this, what my mother was buying.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there was the wife of the storekeeper, and she said to my mother that I am looking like a Jew.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she said-- this is in Polish-- like-- like our nation.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I didn't pay to this attention because all the time I was used to it that some people they thought that I am Jewish boy.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my mother, she didn't say anything against, but after we were out-- went out of the store, she said, why is she saying that you are looking like-- like [INAUDIBLE], like 'our?' So why are they are thinking that only Jewish people are better than Polish people?",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And yeah, that-- that was a-- such an illustration.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why she said that I am looking like theirs is probably that I was a little bit shy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was not arrogant.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I had good manners, and such things.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
